# Required Tableau Sheets

## 1. Sales Trend View

### Purpose

Show how sales change over time.

### Recommended Visualization

Line Chart

### Configuration

* Columns: Order Date (Month or Quarter)
* Rows: SUM(Sales)
* Color: Year (optional)

### Business Insight

This view helps identify:

* Growth trends
* Seasonal patterns
* Peak sales periods
* Declining sales periods

---

## 2. Regional Performance View

### Purpose

Compare sales and profit across regions or states.

### Recommended Visualization

Filled Map or Bar Chart

### Configuration

Option A: Region Analysis

* Rows: Region
* Columns: SUM(Sales)
* Color: SUM(Profit)

Option B: State Map

* State on map
* Size: Sales
* Color: Profit

### Business Insight

This view identifies:

* High-performing regions
* Low-performing regions
* Geographic profit differences

---

## 3. Category Profitability View

### Purpose

Evaluate category and sub-category performance.

### Recommended Visualization

Horizontal Bar Chart

### Configuration

* Rows: Category, Sub-Category
* Columns: SUM(Profit)
* Color: Profit Margin

### Business Insight

This view helps identify:

* Most profitable categories
* Loss-making categories
* Product areas requiring attention

---

## 4. Customer Segment View

### Purpose

Compare business performance across customer segments.

### Recommended Visualization

Side-by-Side Bar Chart

### Configuration

* Columns: Customer Segment
* Rows: SUM(Sales)
* Secondary Measure: SUM(Profit)

### Business Insight

This view identifies:

* Highest-value customer groups
* Most profitable segments
* Segment-specific opportunities

---

## 5. Shipping Performance View

### Purpose

Analyze delivery performance and shipping efficiency.

### Recommended Visualization

Bar Chart

### Configuration

* Rows: Shipping Delay Bucket
* Columns: AVG(Delivery Days)
* Color: Ship Mode

Alternative:

* Rows: Ship Mode
* Columns: AVG(Delivery Days)

### Business Insight

This view identifies:

* Fastest shipping methods
* Delivery bottlenecks
* Operational improvement opportunities

---

## 6. Discount vs Profit View

### Purpose

Analyze the relationship between discounts and profitability.

### Recommended Visualization

Scatter Plot

### Configuration

* Columns: Discount
* Rows: Profit
* Detail: Order ID
* Color: Category

### Business Insight

This view helps determine:

* Whether discounts improve performance
* Whether high discounts reduce profitability
* Optimal discount levels

---

## 7. Return Analysis View

### Purpose

Understand return behavior across the business.

### Recommended Visualization

Bar Chart

### Configuration

Option A

* Rows: Category
* Columns: SUM(Return Flag)

Option B

* Rows: Customer Segment
* Columns: SUM(Return Flag)

Option C

* Rows: Region
* Columns: SUM(Return Flag)

### Business Insight

This view identifies:

* Categories with high returns
* Regions with high return rates
* Customer segments generating more returns

